<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n12009g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12009g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12009g"> 9(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> une (id&eacute;esse)</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">La Vie, ce n&apos;est pas ce que j&apos;appelle <mark>une id&eacute;e</mark> claire; mais enfin les desecendants de Voltaire en ont fait <mark>une d&eacute;esse</mark>, et se contentent fort bien de cette id&eacute;e-l&agrave;. Ils la d&eacute;fendent, comme si elle &eacute;tait menac&eacute;e, comme si des gens risquaient de prendre la mort pour idole! <br><font color="green">[Life is not what I would call a clear idea; but still the descendants of Voltaire have made a goddess out of her, and they are well pleased with that particular idea. They defend it as if it were under threat, as if people ran the risk of idolizing death!]</font> <small> Jacques Boulenger &amp; Andr&eacute; Th&eacute;rive, <a name="SOIR" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SOIR"><cite title="source">Les Soir&eacute;es du Grammaire-Club</cite></a> (1924) 146</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: Fr. <i>id&eacute;e</i>: idea; <i>d&eacute;esse</i>: goddess. </mm> </dd></dl>
